      "category": "getting-started",
      "title": "Before first use and control panel",
      "excerpt": "4 ninjakitchen.com3 ninjakitchen.com GETTING TO KNOW YOUR NINJA CRISPI™ 1 Remove and discard any packaging material, stickers, and tape from the unit. 2 Remove all accessories from the package and read this manual carefu…",
      "text": "4 ninjakitchen.com3 ninjakitchen.com GETTING TO KNOW YOUR NINJA CRISPI™ 1 Remove and discard any packaging material, stickers, and tape from the unit. 2 Remove all accessories from the package and read this manual carefully. Please pay particular attention to operational instructions, warnings, and important safeguards to avoid any injury or property damage. 3 Wash the containers, adapter, crisper plates, and lids in hot, soapy water, then rinse and dry thoroughly. NEVER clean the PowerPod in the dishwasher. BEFORE FIRST USE FUNCTION BUTTONS RECRISP: Revive leftovers by gently warming them, leaving you with crispy results. AIR FRY: Use to give food crispiness and crunch with little to no oil. MAX CRISP: Blast your food with high heat for the ultimate crisp. Best for prepackaged frozen foods. BAKE: Create decadent baked treats and desserts. OPERATING BUTTONS START/POWER button: Press to turn the PowerPod on. When the PowerPod is attached to a container, press to start or stop cooking. Press and hold for 2 seconds to turn off the PowerPod. MODE button: Press to cycle through to desired function. TIME - and + buttons: Use to adjust the cook time in any function before or during cooking. NOTE: Functions may vary by model. USE & CARE GUIDE POWERPOD™ 1 The PowerPod should NEVER be used on any container or vessel other than the Ninja glass container. 2 The PowerPod should NEVER be used when not on a Ninja glass container. 3 When placing PowerPod on the Ninja glass container, ALWAYS ensure easy-grip handles are aligned with the sides of the pod, NOT the front and back. 4 PowerPod will pause automatically when removed from the Ninja glass container. To resume cooking, place the PowerPod back on the Ninja glass container and press the START/POWER button. 5 NEVER remove the finger guard from the PowerPod. 6 All items should be kept 6 inches away from the PowerPod vent when the unit is in use. 7 PowerPod feet allow you to place the PowerPod directly on any countertop after use. CONTAINER LIDS 1 Lids are freezer safe, microwave safe (ensure lid is NOT sealed on Ninja glass container when in the microwave), and dishwasher safe (top rack only). 2 DO NOT seal lid on Ninja glass container directly after cooking. 3 NEVER place PowerPod, Ninja glass container, or crisper plate directly on lid after cooking. CRISPER PLATES 1 Crisper plates are dishwasher safe, but they are NOT microwave or oven safe. ADAPTER 1 Adapter should be used with the PowerPod ONLY when cooking in the 4-qt or 2.5-qt Ninja glass containers. 2 Adapter is dishwasher safe, but it is NOT microwave or oven safe. NOTE: Cease all use of PowerPod if any feet are broken or damaged. NINJA GLASS CONTAINERS 1 Heat-protectant base and easy-grip handles are fixed permanently to the Ninja glass containers and should NEVER be removed. 2 Cease using Ninja glass container if easy-grip handles or heat protectant base are broken or damaged. 3 Ninja glass containers are freezer safe, microwave safe, and dishwasher safe. 4 Ninja glass containers are NOT oven/stovetop safe. 5 Handle Ninja glass containers with care. They can break if dropped, hit hard against a surface, or struck with a hard utensil. 6 If a Ninja glass container becomes chipped, cracked, or deeply scratched, DO NOT use, as container strength may be compromised and the container could break or shatter. NOTE If a piece of a Ninja glass container chips or breaks off, use thick gloves and caution while cleaning up the glass, as pieces may be sharp. Dispose of glass in a standard waste bin; DO NOT recycle. NOTE Adapter should NEVER be used when cooking with the 5-cup or 6-cup Ninja glass containers. 3 Adapter will be hot after use; allow it to cool for 10 minutes before handling it. HOW TO USE YOUR ADAPTER ASSEMBLY 1 Place PowerPod into adapter, ensuring the 4 feet on the PowerPod are aligned with the four corners of the adapter. 2 Push PowerPod down until you feel the adapter click onto the PowerPod. 3 Place now assembled PowerPod and adapter onto large Ninja glass container. REMOVAL 1 PowerPod and adapter will be hot after cooking, allow both to cool for 10 minutes before interacting. 2 Grip the top of the PowerPod with one hand and use the other hand to grasp the front tab of the adapter. 3 Push down on the tab while lifting the PowerPod. PowerPod should easily lift off of the adapter. To resume cooking, place the PowerPod back on the Ninja glass container and press the START/POWER button. NOTE Push PowerPod slightly back while pulling up for seamless removal."
